<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Advanced placement and cademic credit toward a degree may be granted to students who receive a grade of 3, 4, or 5 on the Advanced Placement Examinations of the College Entrance Examination Board. Students with a grade of 3 will receive a maximum of three semester hours of credit.  Students receiving grades of 4 or 5 may receive up to six semester hours credit.Credit is awarded only in those fields applicable to the Bluefield College curriculum.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.bluefield.edu/academic-catalog" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

